<p>Since isFileScaleUsed is Read-only, this script detects the File Scale and Recalculates the Scale Factor( Global Scale) accordingly.</p>  <pre><code>using UnityEditor;   public class FBXScaleFix : AssetPostprocessor {   public void OnPreprocessModel()   {   ModelImporter modelImporter = (ModelImporter)assetImporter;   modelImporter.globalScale = 1.0f / modelImporter.fileScale;   UnityEngine.Debug.Log("Import file scale: " + modelImporter.fileScale + ", global scale: " + modelImporter.globalScale);    } } </code></pre>  <p>Problem is that OnPreprocessModel fileScale is detected as 1 but it shows after 0.01 ( example number )</p>  <p>But if you change any setting inside inspector the object Scale Factor( Global Scale) scales to normal value, in this example 100</p>  <p>This doesn't work either</p>  <pre><code>  public void OnPostprocessModel() {    ModelImporter modelImporter = (ModelImporter)assetImporter;    importer.importMaterials = false;  } </code></pre>  <p>Does anyone know a solution to this?</p>